  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add the <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ground coriander</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cumin</strong>, a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and <strong>salt </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> to a plate and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>Cajun-style spice mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1691483833463-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1691483833463-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1691483833463-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1691483833463-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1691483833463-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Press one side of the <strong>chicken breast portions</strong> into the <strong>Cajun-style spice mix </strong>and save the rest of the spice mix for later – this is your <strong>Cajun-style spiced</strong> <strong>chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1691483836075-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1691483836075-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1691483836075-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1691483836075-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1691483836075-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>Cajun-style spiced</strong> <strong>chicken</strong>, spice-side down, and cook for 3 min or until slightly charred</p><p>Once charred, transfer the chicken, spice-side up, to a baking tray and reserve the pan for later</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the juices run clear</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
