    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> pepper strips</strong> and <strong>remaining Cajun-style spice mix </strong>and cook for 8-10 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and <strong>soft cheese</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>creamy stock</strong></p>",
